<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<bpmn:definitions xmlns:bpmn="http://www.omg.org/spec/BPMN/20100524/MODEL"
                  xmlns:bpmndi="http://www.omg.org/spec/BPMN/20100524/DI"
                  xmlns:dc="http://www.omg.org/spec/DD/20100524/DC"
                  xmlns:di="http://www.omg.org/spec/DD/20100524/DI"
                  id="Definitions_E05AutoCreate" targetNamespace="http://bpmn.io/schema/bpmn">
  <bpmn:collaboration id="Collaboration_E05AutoCreate">
    <bpmn:participant id="Participant_E05AutoCreate" name="e05 - Auto-create Supplier or Item from Free-text Reference" processRef="Process_E05AutoCreate" />
  </bpmn:collaboration>
  <bpmn:process id="Process_E05AutoCreate" isExecutable="false">
    <bpmn:laneSet id="LaneSet_E05AutoCreate">
      <bpmn:lane id="L_req" name="Requester">
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>Start</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
      </bpmn:lane>
      <bpmn:lane id="L_buyer" name="Procurement / Buyer">
      </bpmn:lane>
      <bpmn:lane id="L_sys" name="Platform / System">
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>ParseRefs</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>Fork</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>GwSupplierKind</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>LookupSupplier</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>GwSupplierFound</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>CreateSupplier</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>GwItemKind</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>LookupItem</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>GwItemFound</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>CreateItem</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>Join</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>LinkAndPersist</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>AuditEmit</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>Reject</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
        <bpmn:flowNodeRef>End</bpmn:flowNodeRef>
      </bpmn:lane>
    </bpmn:laneSet>
    <bpmn:startEvent id="Start" name="Submit requisition / PO with references">
      <bpmn:documentation>Trigger: a requester (or buyer on a PO) submits a document whose supplier reference and each line item reference may be EITHER an existing record's UUID OR a free-text name typed into the search box. The entity normalizer must resolve every reference before the document is written. Supplier reference is optional on a requisition (a requester may not know the supplier); item references on the lines are required (a line must name a thing). [SCOR S1.1 | ISO 7.5 | source: RA entity normalizer e09 + auto-create]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f1</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:startEvent>
    <bpmn:serviceTask id="ParseRefs" name="Classify each reference: UUID vs free-text">
      <bpmn:documentation>For each reference the normalizer tests the format. Expression: value matches UUID regex (8-4-4-4-12 hex) -&gt; treat as an existing-record id (LOOKUP path). Else value is a non-empty string -&gt; treat as a new free-text name (AUTO-CREATE path, NO lookup is attempted). isEmpty rule: null/blank/[]/{} is empty (rejected as a missing required field for items; allowed-null for the optional supplier). The supplier reference and the item references are resolved on two PARALLEL branches that join before linking. [SCOR OE2 | ISO 7.5 | source: RA field engine normalizer + e09 resolver]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f1</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f2</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:serviceTask>
    <bpmn:parallelGateway id="Fork" name="Resolve supplier and items in parallel">
      <bpmn:documentation>Parallel split. Branch A resolves the optional supplier reference; Branch B resolves the required item references on the lines. Both must complete (and any lookup must succeed) before linking. A 404 on ANY UUID lookup on EITHER branch rejects the WHOLE operation (atomic; nothing is written). [SCOR OE2 | source: RA parallel resolve + atomic reject]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f2</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f3</bpmn:outgoing>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f4</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:parallelGateway>
    <bpmn:exclusiveGateway id="GwSupplierKind" name="Supplier ref: UUID, free-text, or null?">
      <bpmn:documentation>Branch A. Expression: supplierRef == null -&gt; no supplier on this requisition (allowed; skip). supplierRef matches UUID -&gt; lookup existing supplier. supplierRef is free-text -&gt; auto-create. The supplier link is OPTIONAL, so a null is a valid join input. [SCOR S1.6 | source: RA optional supplier link]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f3</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f5</bpmn:outgoing>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f6</bpmn:outgoing>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f7</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:exclusiveGateway>
    <bpmn:serviceTask id="LookupSupplier" name="Look up supplier by id">
      <bpmn:documentation>GET supplier by UUID. Found -&gt; use the existing supplierId (any status). NOT found -&gt; 404; this is a dangling id (400/404 class), not an auto-create, and it REJECTS THE WHOLE OPERATION (no partial write). Distinction (RA e09): a missing resolver = 500 config defect; a dangling id supplied by the client = 4xx reject. [SCOR S1.6 | source: RA e09 dangling-id reject]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f5</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f8</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:serviceTask>
    <bpmn:exclusiveGateway id="GwSupplierFound" name="Supplier id resolves?">
      <bpmn:documentation>Expression: lookup returned a record. True -&gt; carry existing supplierId to the join. False -&gt; raise 404 and abort the entire submission (atomic). A UUID is asserted to exist; it is never auto-created. [SCOR S1.6 | source: RA atomic reject]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f8</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f9</bpmn:outgoing>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f10</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:exclusiveGateway>
    <bpmn:serviceTask id="CreateSupplier" name="Auto-create supplier (S/##### , PENDING_ONBOARDING)">
      <bpmn:documentation>Free-text supplier name -&gt; create a new Supplier with code from the configurable sequence S/##### (first ever is S/00001, then S/00002, monotonically; pattern configurable per tenant). Fields seeded: name = the typed text, status = PENDING_ONBOARDING (default), currency = document currency, all qualification fields empty (certs/COA/AVL/risk to be completed at onboarding 06). NO lookup is performed for a free-text name. Carries the new supplierId to the join. [SCOR S1.6 | ISO 8.4.1 | source: RA auto-create + S/##### code]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f6</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f11</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:serviceTask>
    <bpmn:exclusiveGateway id="GwItemKind" name="Each item ref: UUID or free-text?">
      <bpmn:documentation>Branch B, per line. Expression: itemRef is required (non-empty) else 400 missing-field on that line. itemRef matches UUID -&gt; lookup existing item. itemRef is free-text -&gt; auto-create. Lines are required, so unlike the supplier there is no null-skip path here. [SCOR OE4 | source: RA required item lines]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f4</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f12</bpmn:outgoing>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f13</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:exclusiveGateway>
    <bpmn:serviceTask id="LookupItem" name="Look up item(s) by id">
      <bpmn:documentation>GET item by UUID for each UUID line. Found -&gt; use existing itemId and auto-populated description (RA description auto-populate). NOT found -&gt; 404 dangling id -&gt; REJECT THE WHOLE OPERATION. [SCOR OE4 | source: RA e09 dangling-id reject]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f12</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f14</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:serviceTask>
    <bpmn:exclusiveGateway id="GwItemFound" name="All item ids resolve?">
      <bpmn:documentation>Expression: every UUID line returned a record. True -&gt; carry itemIds to the join. False -&gt; 404 and abort the whole submission (atomic). [SCOR OE4 | source: RA atomic reject]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f14</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f15</bpmn:outgoing>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f16</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:exclusiveGateway>
    <bpmn:serviceTask id="CreateItem" name="Auto-create item(s) (DEP/SG/SSG/000001, PENDING_ONBOARDING)">
      <bpmn:documentation>Each free-text item name -&gt; create a new Item with code from the configurable segmented sequence DEP/SG/SSG/000001 (department / segment / sub-segment / 6-digit running number; first in a sub-segment is ...000001). Fields seeded: description = typed text, status = PENDING_ONBOARDING (default), stockUom/purchaseUom default, segment/subSegment from the chosen path, sourcePriority default PURCHASED. NO lookup for a free-text name. Carries new itemIds to the join. [SCOR OE4 | source: RA item code + auto-create]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f13</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f17</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:serviceTask>
    <bpmn:parallelGateway id="Join" name="Join: both branches resolved">
      <bpmn:documentation>Parallel join. Proceeds only when Branch A (supplier: existing id, new id, or null) AND Branch B (all item ids: existing or new) have BOTH completed with no 404. If either branch raised a dangling-id 404, the operation has already aborted and the join is never reached (nothing written). [SCOR OE2 | source: RA join-before-link]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f7</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:incoming>f9</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:incoming>f11</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:incoming>f15</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:incoming>f17</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f18</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:parallelGateway>
    <bpmn:serviceTask id="LinkAndPersist" name="Link refs and persist requisition / PO in one transaction">
      <bpmn:documentation>In a single transaction: write the requisition/PO with the resolved supplierId (or null) on the header and the resolved itemIds on the lines. Any newly created supplier/item rows are committed in the SAME transaction as the document (all-or-nothing). [SCOR S1.1/S2.1 | ISO 7.5 | source: RA transactional link]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f18</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f19</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:serviceTask>
    <bpmn:serviceTask id="AuditEmit" name="Audit auto-creates + emit SSE + notify">
      <bpmn:documentation>Write append-only audit entries (category supplier / item / requisition): each auto-create logged with its new code and PENDING_ONBOARDING status; emit SSE {supplierId}/{itemId}/{requisitionId}; fire supplier-approval-requested / item-approval-requested notifications so the new masters enter the onboarding queue (06/07). [SCOR OE4 | ISO 7.5 | source: platform-services audit + notifications]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f19</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>f20</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:serviceTask>
    <bpmn:endEvent id="Reject" name="Reject whole operation (404 dangling id)">
      <bpmn:documentation>Terminal error path. A UUID reference that does not resolve raises 404 and aborts the entire submission with no partial write (atomic). The requester/buyer sees the failing reference and corrects it. Distinct from a missing resolver (500 config defect). [SCOR OE2 | source: RA e09 atomic reject]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f10</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:incoming>f16</bpmn:incoming>
    </bpmn:endEvent>
    <bpmn:endEvent id="End" name="Document persisted; new masters PENDING_ONBOARDING">
      <bpmn:documentation>Requisition/PO persisted with resolved links; any auto-created supplier/item awaits onboarding/approval (PENDING_ONBOARDING -&gt; PENDING_APPROVAL -&gt; ONBOARDED). Ordering against a PENDING_ONBOARDING supplier is gated downstream (06). [SCOR S1.1 | source: RA lifecycle]</bpmn:documentation>
      <bpmn:incoming>f20</bpmn:incoming>
    </bpmn:endEvent>
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f1" sourceRef="Start" targetRef="ParseRefs" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f2" sourceRef="ParseRefs" targetRef="Fork" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f3" name="Branch A: supplier" sourceRef="Fork" targetRef="GwSupplierKind" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f4" name="Branch B: items" sourceRef="Fork" targetRef="GwItemKind" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f5" name="UUID" sourceRef="GwSupplierKind" targetRef="LookupSupplier" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f6" name="free-text name" sourceRef="GwSupplierKind" targetRef="CreateSupplier" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f7" name="null (optional link skipped)" sourceRef="GwSupplierKind" targetRef="Join" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f8" sourceRef="LookupSupplier" targetRef="GwSupplierFound" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f9" name="found: existing supplierId" sourceRef="GwSupplierFound" targetRef="Join" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f10" name="404 -&gt; abort whole op" sourceRef="GwSupplierFound" targetRef="Reject" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f11" sourceRef="CreateSupplier" targetRef="Join" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f12" name="UUID" sourceRef="GwItemKind" targetRef="LookupItem" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f13" name="free-text name" sourceRef="GwItemKind" targetRef="CreateItem" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f14" sourceRef="LookupItem" targetRef="GwItemFound" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f15" name="all resolve: existing itemIds" sourceRef="GwItemFound" targetRef="Join" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f16" name="404 -&gt; abort whole op" sourceRef="GwItemFound" targetRef="Reject" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f17" sourceRef="CreateItem" targetRef="Join" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f18" sourceRef="Join" targetRef="LinkAndPersist" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f19" sourceRef="LinkAndPersist" targetRef="AuditEmit" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="f20" sourceRef="AuditEmit" targetRef="End" />
    <bpmn:textAnnotation id="NoteAutoCreate">
      <bpmn:text>UUID reference = assert-exists (lookup; a 404 rejects the whole operation atomically, no partial write). Free-text reference = auto-create with no lookup. Supplier code S/##### (first S/00001); item code DEP/SG/SSG/000001; both default PENDING_ONBOARDING. Supplier link is optional (null allowed); item lines are required. Supplier and items resolve on parallel branches that join before the document is linked and persisted in one transaction.</bpmn:text>
    </bpmn:textAnnotation>
    <bpmn:association id="Assoc_E05AutoCreate_1" sourceRef="Join" targetRef="NoteAutoCreate" />
  </bpmn:process>
  <bpmndi:BPMNDiagram id="Diagram_E05AutoCreate">
    <bpmndi:BPMNPlane id="Plane_E05AutoCreate" bpmnElement="Collaboration_E05AutoCreate">
